ral world. It mixes visual and literary genres to give the reader a sensory and affective experience of a thought-world that is very different from our own. An experimental intellectual history, Life invites readers into the premodern cosmos to experience a world that is at once familiar, strange, and deeply compelling.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aSpiritualityxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520400696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520400696/original  a978-3-11-079135-8  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles